Preamble

Hasse Cyber Security has released this licence to promote collaboration among hardware designers and to provide a legal tool for the dissemination of hardware designs.

The Hasse Cyber Security Open Hardware Licence Version 2 – Permissive is intended to maximise the ability of individuals, researchers, companies, and manufacturers to use hardware designs, including commercial applications, with minimal obligations.

This licence is focused on the design itself and on ensuring proper credit while allowing others to build, improve, manufacture, and distribute the design.

Terms and Conditions

Definitions

“Design” means the design documentation for hardware licensed under this Licence, in any format or medium.

“Documentation” means all materials describing the Design, including schematics, netlists, PCB layout files, bills of materials, drawings, specifications, firmware interfaces, and related materials.

“Hardware” means any physical device embodying the Design or any part thereof.

“Modification” means any change, improvement, adaptation, or derivative of the Design.

“Product” means any hardware, assembly, or commercial item based wholly or partly on the Design.

“Source” means the preferred form of the Design for making Modifications.

“Licence” means this Hasse Cyber Security Open Hardware Licence Version 2 – Permissive.

“Licensor” means Hasse Cyber Security.

“You” means any person or entity exercising rights under this Licence.

Grant of Rights

The Licensor grants You a worldwide, royalty-free, perpetual, non-exclusive licence to:

a) use the Design and Documentation;
b) study and modify the Design;
c) copy and distribute the Design;
d) manufacture Hardware implementing the Design;
e) sell Products based on the Design;
f) sublicense Products incorporating the Design;
g) otherwise deal in the Design without restriction,

subject to the conditions below.

